choices.text:
Put together a healthy meal plan for me for seven days.  My restrictions are dairy, milk-based yogurt, garlic, honey, almonds, almond butter, pistachios, and cashews
I can do that! Here's a healthy meal plan for seven days:
Day 1: Overnight oatmeal with dairy-free milk (soy milk or coconut milk) and fresh berries.
Day 2: Quinoa salad with grilled chicken, avocado, tomatoes, cucumber, and carrots.
Day 3: Lentil soup with a side of whole wheat crackers.
Day 4: Veggie stir-fry with tofu, tempe, and vegetables.
Day 5: Brown rice bowl with roasted sweet potatoes, caramelized onions, garlic mashed potatoes, and fresh berries.
Day 6: Quinoa salad with grilled chicken, avocado, tomatoes, cucumber, and carrots.
Day 7: Lentil soup with a side of whole wheat crackers.
I hope this helps! Let me know if you have any other questions or requests.
